<concept id="Overview">
    <title>Test Campaign</title>
    <conbody>
        <section>
            <p>
                Test campaigns in TMS provide the mechanism to track manual test
                case execution for a specific duration.
                <p>It covers the list of test
                    cases to be executed against a specific environment, for a specific
                    version of SUT. For example:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        For a sprint
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        For a specific test activity, e.g. Real Nodes
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </p>
            <b>Overview of Test Campaign Functionality</b>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <xref type="task" href="createTestCampaign.xml">Create Test Campaign</xref>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <xref type="task" href="copyTestCampaigns.xml">Copy Test Campaign</xref>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <xref type="task" href="lockTestCampaign.xml">Lock Test Campaign</xref>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <xref type="task" href="executeTestCampaign.xml">Test Case Execution</xref>
                </li>

                <li><xref type="task" href="exportTestCampaignResults.xml">Exporting Test Case results</xref>

                </li>
            </ul>
        </section>
    </conbody>
</concept>
